OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright start in the east, but
OL,6,Frather cloudy with showery outbreaks
OL,7,Fof rain further west. The showers
OL,8,Fbecoming more widespread from mid-
OL,9,Fafternoon, and turning persistent from
OL,10,Fthe southeast later. Still rather warm
OL,11,Fand humid.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FRain will become persistent
OL,14,Fovernight with some heavier bursts
OL,15,Flikely across eastern counties. The
OL,16,Frain should clear southern counties
OL,17,Ffor a time towards dawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
